  "name": "ring-valley",
  "description": "Three settlements strung along a corridor. Every road is a symmetric pair of edges carrying opposite tags, so nothing moves unless a transport transform pulls it along a direction. Buildings are catalysts, which is what caps each job's throughput. The town mints nudges from a control terminal; the forest preaches a back-to-the-land movement that ships downstream and nudges the town's stack with no player involved.",
